Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.39,0:12:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,benevolence of divinity is that by one's\Nown choice, one determines one's own
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.12,0:13:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic destiny,\Nnot some arbitrary god who hates you and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.36,0:13:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,throws you into hell or beats you up.\NMost of the religions of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.04,0:13:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,believe in a god who beats you up, you\Nknow, even bad. Boom, boom, boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you get to determine it yourself. So\Nthe freedom then to realize the source
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own existence is that you have\Ninfinite freedom than infinite freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is there's no limit upon your choice and\Nthat you are reborn as the Buddhist said
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.04,0:13:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no greater\Nthing to be grateful for for the
